uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model

Interface IValue

  • All Superinterfaces:
    FEntity
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CFrame, IDataValue, IFrame, INumber, IString

    public interface IValue
extends FEntity
    Represents an entity that can be the value for an instance-level slot. Value-entities can be either instance-level or concept-level.

      • subsumes

        boolean subsumes(IValue other)
        Tests whether this value-entity subsumes another specified value-entity. This will be the case if and only if the value-entities are equal, or if this value-entity represents a set of some kind, of which the other value-entity is either a member, or represents a sub-set.
        Parameters:
        other - Other value-entity to test for subsumption
        Returns:
        True if this value-entity subsumes other value-entity

      • equalsStructure

        boolean equalsStructure(IValue other)
        Tests whether this value-entity currently has a structure that is equivalent to another value-entity. For immutable value-entities the result will be fixed, and will be the same as the result of the equals(java.lang.Object) method, whereas for mutable entities the result will vary, being dependent on the current configurations of the respective value-entities.
        Parameters:
        other - Other value-entity to test for structure-matching with this one
        Returns:
        true if structures match

      • subsumesStructure

        boolean subsumesStructure(IValue other)
        Tests whether this value-entity currently has a structure that subsumes that of another value-entity. For immutable value-entities the result will be fixed, and will be the same as the result of the subsumes(uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.IValue) method, whereas for mutable entities the result will vary, being dependent on the current configurations of the respective value-entities.
        Parameters:
        other - Other value-entity to test for structure-subsumption with this one
        Returns:
        true if structures match

      • structuralHashCode

        int structuralHashCode()
        Calculates an integer-value based on the current structure of the value-entity, suitable for use as a hash-code value for any wrapper-class that is to use the equalsStructure(uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.IValue) method in it's implementation of the general Object.equals(java.lang.Object) method. For immutable value-entities the result will be fixed, and will be the same as the result of the hashCode() method, whereas for mutable entities the result will vary, being dependent on the current configurations of the respective value-entities.
        Returns:
        Suitable structure-based hash-code value
